  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "A large crag on the eastern shore of Åmunsfjärd, the narrow bay that extends about 1 km south of Östnorabadet and a couple of km north of Landfjärden. Here you’ll find some massive overhangs, a steeper version of Tunabergs, and plenty of additional rock. The routes furthest right on Tvåbultsväggen and Examensväggen are on private land. Do not climb there!",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:ostnoraberget"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A large crag on the eastern shore of Åmunsfjärd, the narrow bay that runs in about 1 km south of Östnorabadet and a couple of km north of Landfjärden. Here you’ll find some massive overhangs, a steeper version of Tunabergs, and plenty of rock beyond that. The routes on the left side of Tvåbultsväggen and Examensväggen are on private property. Do not climb there!",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "miljo": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Environment",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "South-facing, open location. The left walls tend to be damp.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "From Stockholm, take the motorway (73) towards Nynäshamn for just under 10 km south of Västerhaninge. Exit at the sign for \"Tungelsta Landfjärden\" and cross the motorway, then turn right towards Landfjärden. After a few hundred meters, turn left at the Östnora camping sign. After about 700 m, a private road goes off to the right. Follow it (on foot) for 300 m and take the right fork. After another 500 m, the road ends at some boathouses. The rock is directly in front.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kommunikationer": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Transport",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Buses 847 and 849 run from Västerhaninge and travel along Nynäsvägen past the crag.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "access": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Parts of the crag (Tvåbultsväggen and Examensväggen) are on private property where climbing is not allowed.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "franska-vaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "French Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Bulbous and water-polished. The first wall you encounter.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "forsta-taket": {
          "title": {
            "text": "First Roof",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "tangavaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Tang Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A couple of projects are underway in the middle of the wall. An unidentified route goes up the right side. Above and to the right of Tang Wall, Thorsell has put up a short overhang (4+).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "toppsvaet": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Top Overhang",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ostnoraberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "There are two overhang routes to the top of the entire massif, graded 3. From the campsite, climb the overhang slab past the start of the route Överhänget and continue to the base. An old bolt is at the top.",
